ze=1> WARNING: Long post.<br>
<br>
I have two requests before you continue.  First, you read the whole thing before you reply.  If you cannot commit to reading the whole thing, please come back when you can.  It shouldn't take more than five minutes, but sometimes that's enough to throw a monkey wrench in your plans.  Second, post constructive, calm, insightful comments.  Don't tell me, &quot;Zesty, this sucks,&quot; without saying WHY it sucks.  Maybe not everything sucks....maybe its something that can be fixed so that this would work.  <br>
<br>
Whereever I felt that an explanation was necessary, it is in parentheses.  I will endeavor to keep this to a minimum.  The second message in this thread contains what I perceive to be the &quot;pros and cons&quot; of this system.  Thank you for reading.<br>
<br>
<br>
PROPOSED &quot;UBERMOB&quot; ROTATION PROCEDURE<br>
<br>
Rotation lists for mobs with extensively long spawn times on the Brell Serilis server shall be subject to the following rules:<br>
<br>
<br>
1. ROTATION LISTS<br>
<br>
     A -- All rotation lists, regardless of mob spawn time, are limited to 10 spots in size.  Presently, Brell rotates Vox, Nagafen, Venril Sathir, and Trakanon.  With the introduction of the Scars of Velious expansion, more rotated mobs may be discovered.  As these are found, additional rotation lists will be added as necessary.  <br>
<br>
     B -- Initial rotation lists for this procedure shall be taken from the existing open rotation logs of the Brell Serilis message board.  The top ten reservations for each mob shall be retained and all others deleted subject to the new procedure.  (Yes, I know, if you're number 11 on the list, this absolutely sucks.  But I had to start somewhere.  Lists of 12 seemed to me too long, lists of 8 too short, for what I had in mind here.)<br>
<br>
<br>
2. ROTATION LISTS -- WHO CAN BE ON THEM<br>
<br>
     A -- In order to be added to any rotation list, individuals signing up MUST disclose the following: <br>
     Full Character Name<br>
     Character Level<br>
     Guild affiliation, if any.<br>
Failure to disclose this information or deliberately falsifying this information (For example, Joe says he's not in a guild when he is so that he can hold an independent spot on the list.) will result in the individual not being added to the rotation list, or, in the case of any individual who has already been added, the revocation of the reservation in question.<br>
<br>
     B -- All spots in all rotations which are requested by guilded individuals are considered to be held by THAT GUILD, regardless of the intention of the claim.  In the event that the individual who claimed a guild spot in any rotation leaves that guild, either willingly or unwillingly, the spot in the rotation is retained by the guild and the guild's leader becomes the default raid organizer.  In the event that any guild on a rotation list is disbanded, all spots on all rotation lists held by the guild in question are vacated. <br>
<br>
     C -- Any rotation spot held by an unguilded individual is considered to be an INDEPENDENT RAID.  The individual who holds this rotation spot is considered an Independent Raid Organizer (IRO).  At least ONE, but no more than FOUR, spot(s) on each rotation MUST be held by IRO's.  If no IRO signs up for a rotation where no independent raid is presently in line, the 10th spot in that rotation shall be held in abeyance pending the appearance of an IRO to claim the position.  EXCEPTION: If an IRO's raid in any rotation has been conducted, there need be no independent raid in that rotation until sign ups for that particular rotation spot are once again being accepted.<br>
<br>
     D -- No guild may hold spots on more than two rotation lists, or more than one spot on any single rotation list.  No IRO may hold more than one spot on all combined rotation lists.  (This would be increased as more rotation lists are created for Velious, and, subsequently, VP.)  <br>
<br>
     E -- In the event any IRO becomes guilded while he/she holds spots on existing rotation lists, those spots are thereafter held by the individual's new guild assuming this does not violate 2D.  In the event that a previously unguilded IRO becomes a member of a guild and that guild thereafter violates rule 2D, the IRO's raids shall be eliminated by the forum moderator, one at a time, until the guild is once again in compliance with these rules.  (I would consult with the guild in question prior to the elimination of any spots if there was a question as to which to eliminate.)<br>
<br>
     F -- With the exception of rule E, above, all spots on all rotation lists are non-transferable.  If you sign up to run a raid as an IRO, you are the raid organizer.  Not somebody else.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
3.  ROTATION LISTS -- CREATION, MAINTENANCE, AND SIGN UP PERIOD<br>
<br>
     A -- The Brell Serilis Raid Forums moderator is responsible for the creation and maintenance of all rotation lists required by these rules.<br>
<br>
     B -- At any time when there are open spots on a given rotation list, the Raid Forums moderator may, at his or her option, open a thread in the sign ups forum of the Brell Board to fill those vacancies.  Spots on a rotation list may ONLY be filled by replying to the moderator's thread.  All spots on these rotations shall be filled on a first-come-first-served basis assuming they are in compliance with all the guidelines in rule 2.  The moderator should NOT attempt to keep all lists full at all times.  Ideally, between 2 and 5 vacancies should exist on a given list before further sign ups are accepted.  This is to prevent individuals and guilds from merely claiming thier vacated spot on a rotation list at the conclusion of a successful raid.<br>
<br>
     C -- You may ONLY sign up for yourself (if independent) or your guild (if guilded.)  Signups which say things like &quot;Jack Sprat the cleric would like to be added to the list....thanks very much....Sincerely, Joe Blow the Paladin.&quot;  Are invalid sign ups and will be dismissed.<br>
<br>
     D -- THE RAID FORUMS MODERATOR MAY NOT, UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES, ISSUE ADVANCE WARNING TO ANY BRELL SERILIS PLAYER OR GUILD OF HIS/HER INTENTION TO OPEN ROTATION LISTS SIGN UPS.  (Duh....but its best to say these things out loud so no one thinks I'm trying to pull a fast one here.)<br>
<br>
     E -- A thread in the signups forum called &quot;Rotation Lists -- Cancellations&quot; shall be created by the raid forums moderator.  In the event that a guild or IRO wishes to relinquish his/her/their spot on any rotation list, they will post in this forum and the spot in question shall be relinquished.<br>
<br>
     F -- The cancellations thread shall be locked by the raid forums moderator whenever ANY sign ups for ANY rotation lists are being accepted.  This is to prevent individuals from claiming what they perceive to be more desirable spots on more desirable rotations after hogging spots on &quot;less&quot; desirable rotations.  (To wit: You can't hog a spot on the Naggy list and then suddenly jump ship when you realize you're early enough to grab a spot on Venril's sign ups.  If you want to hold the Naggy spot, you're going to hold it at the expense of your spot on other lists.)<br>
<br>
     G -- Any individual who conspires via use of alternate EZboard accounts or alternate characters to reserve more than the allowable number of rotations spots as outlined in rule 2 shall forfeit ALL of his or her rotation spots upon discovery of the subterfuge.  If that individual is in a guild, that guild shall forfeit ALL of its rotations spots.  (Note...I know it is possible that a guild member could &quot;go rogue&quot; and conspire to screw up his or her guild.  This rule would hopefully never have to be enforced, and if it was, we'd sure talk it over first.)<br>
<br>
<br>
4.  ROTATION LIST MOBS -- KILL PERIODS<br>
<br>
     A -- No IRO or guild may &quot;pass&quot; a turn when they are up on a rotation list.  The mob must either be killed in the proscribed time period, or the spot vacated and killing rights to the mob passed to the next reservation on the list.<br>
<br>
     B -- Mobs shall be dispatched within the following time parameters.  Failure to dispatch a mob within these time parameters voids the rotation list reservation and the right to kill the mob passes to the next IRO or guild on the list.<br>
<br>
VOX/NAGAFEN: Deadline for slaughter, 1159PM pacific time three FULL days after spawn due to previous kill or planned server reset.  Or four FULL days after unplanned server reset or previously unsuccessful raid.<br>
<br>
VENRIL/TRAK: Deadline for slaughter, 1159PM pacific time, two FULL days after spawn due to previous kill or planned server rest.  Or three FULL days after unplanned server reset or previously unsuccessful raid.<br>
<br>
Explanations and Examples:  <br>
<br>
NAGAFEN is due to pop on tuesday around 4pm.  The next guild in line has until FRIDAY at 1159 pacific to kill him.<br>
<br>
NAGAFEN pops due to a patch outage at 230pm on thursday.  The next guild in line has until SUNDAY at 1159 pacific to kill him.<br>
<br>
NAGAFEN raid fails on friday night.  The next guild in line has until TUESDAY at 1159 pacific to kill him.<br>
<br>
NAGAFEN respawns saturday evening due to an unplanned server outage.  The next guild in line has until WEDNESDAY at 1159 pacific to kill him.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
