<br>
PROS:<br>
<br>
-- Large guilds are favored because they have more members available to them who constantly post on these boards; therefore, they have more of a chance to snag an open spot in a rotation list than a small guild.<br>
<br>
--Small guilds are favored because larger guilds and their members are not allowed to hog and monopolize these rare spawns under this system.  No preferential treatment is afforded a larger guild under this system other than the one listed above.  More members = more chances a guild will catch lucky during the sign up period.<br>
<br>
--Smaller guilds are encouraged to form alliances with each other in order to have more &quot;eyes on the board: for open rotation spots.<br>
<br>
--Independents are guaranteed spots in the rotations, thus preserving everyone's right to participate in all aspects of Everquest and controverting the disadvantage they are at since they have only one person (themselves) who can reserve a spot in a rotation.<br>
<br>
--The limitation on the number of threads in which a guild or individual can hold an active spot reduces &quot;list hogging&quot; and encourages everyone to sign up for ONLY those mobs which they actually intend to kill.<br>
<br>
--It is no longer necessary for level 22 characters to place their names on the Nagafen/Vox rotations in a vain attempt to assure themselves the opportunity to kill these epic monsters once they reach the appropriate level of skill.<br>
<br>
<br>
CONS:<br>
<br>
--Potential abuse on the part of the moderator.  (To wit, if I'm the moderator in question, I could tell my guild, &quot;Hey, i'm about to open the Venril sign-ups.  Someone go out there and snag our spot when I do.&quot;  Anyone who knows me at all knows I would never do this, but its best to get this out in the open because I'm sure it will occur to many of you.)<br>
<br>
--The threat of the random.  That is, if luck isn't on your side, you or your guild might hit a &quot;cold spell&quot; where you can't luck up and hit the boards when the sign up threads are open.  This is a risk with any somewhat random system.<br>
<br>
--Board camping:  Although I don't see this happening, someone could conceivably camp the board waiting for the threads to open.  I would personally combat this by opening threads at varied times throughout the day and week when they are needed.  Honestly though, I don't see this as much as a problem.  The first time a board camper finds himself sitting on the Venril thread for 3 solid weeks waiting for it to open, this will be a moot issue.<br>
<br>
That's all I have....thanks for reading. <p><BR>
